President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation for Earth Day, highlighting the importance of addressing climate change and protecting the environment. He emphasizes the need for collective action and cites the progress made in increasing solar and wind energy production, reducing carbon pollution, and working with international partners to reduce greenhouse gas emissions. The proclamation also mentions efforts to increase fuel efficiency, restore public lands, and safeguard water resources. Obama encourages Americans to participate in programs and activities that promote environmental protection and a sustainable future.